enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve generating ID numbers and share common dependencies such as birthday and gender.
The basePart method is used in both generateInvalid and generateValid methods to construct the initial part of the ID number.
The checksum method is invoked within generateInvalid to calculate the checksum for the generated ID number.
The randomGender method is used to determine the gender for the ID number generation, which is a prerequisite for the generateInvalid method.
